cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper describes the design and development of an autonomous robot for precision pollination, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for localization, mapping, and visual perception. The robot also employs path planning and motion control algorithms, which fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of manipulation techniques, which could be related to the field of robotics (cs.RO) or machine learning (cs.MA).
